<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-10-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-10-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890d.00/231: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-10-27T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department advised by Navy Department that destroyers <hi rend="italic">Coghlan</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Lamson</hi> arrived Alexandria
                            on October 26th. It is understood that they will remain there pending
                            further word from you as to whether their presence at Beirut may be
                            required.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>